&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/domains/hohfeldian/terms/hohfeldian-relief/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/domains/hohfeldian/terms/hohfeldian-relief/> ;
  schema:name "Relief" ;
  schema:description "A Relief is a triple (O, h, R) — an office O, a holder h currently in H*_{t*} (the settled binding), and a reason R (for cause, by request, end of tour, emergency) — together with a dissolution act that drives h's role-binding from H*_{t*} to ⊥. The defining structure: relief is the retraction of the section installed by investiture; after relief, the office O exists with its position vacant (the section s_r → h is collapsed to s_r → ⊥). Relief is the inverse morphism of the investiture's I⁺ act: it applies σ_{t*} to dissolve rather than settle the role-binding. Three cases have distinct formal structures: mutual relief (full investiture I⁻ with μ = 1), relief for cause (unilateral dissolution without incoming holder acknowledgement), and emergency succession (the relief is simultaneous with assumption by the successor)." ;
  schema:datePublished "2026-03-20" ;
  schema:dateModified "2026-03-20" ;
  schema:about &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/domains/hohfeldian/terms/hohfeldian-relief/> ;
  rdfs:seeAlso "Investiture, Succession, Office, Duty, Captain, DutyOfficer, Incumbent, HohfeldianPosition, Record, Accountability" ;
  schema:identifier &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/domains/hohfeldian/terms/hohfeldian-relief/> .

